rComments: Prof. Robinson is so nice and approachable. That's the best thing about her. She just has a lot of work ... like pop quizzes, and is a tough marker overall. But she's clear and concise on what she expects and what she teaches. She also does a lot of cool stuff (like movies and other things).

All profs at U of T should be like professor Robinson. She works for her students and makes you want to work, too.   She is super helpful with discussing ideas and with writing, and her classes are fun and rewarding.

Amazing professor, she approached the classes with so much passion and enthusiasm- Its difficult to not enjoy it as much as she does. That being said, she's a super hard marker so make sure you don't have any typos. See her during office hours for feedback, she's always helpful
Fantastic class! the material she chose for us to read was phenomenal and really really enjoyable. Beware though, she is a TOUGH grader and takes marks off even for the smallest of spelling errors.
AMAZING professor. I looked forward to her classes. She's really knowledgeable and enjoys what she does.
Professor Robinson is really great. She is incredibly organized, and her lectures are informative and very interesting.

Good prof, interesting course, but most of your grade comes from rote memorization as opposed to analytical writing. Four quizzes and half of the midterm consisted of pure memorization work. I dont think this is an appropriate way to assess students at a third year level

Expect a lot of readings (more than usual) and keep up with them, or you'll find it easy to fall behind. Study for the quizzes (they are really easy if you remember the names and places of the text). Would highly recommend.
